    • Method Detail

      • changeGoalImmediatly

        protected final void changeGoalImmediatly(GoapState newGoapState)
        This function can be called by a subclass if the efforts of the unit trying to archive a specific goal should be paused to fulfill a more urgent goal. The GoapState is added to the main goal HashSet and changed by the GoapAgent.

        IMPORTANT:

        The function must only be called once per two update cycles. The reason for this is that the function pushes an IdleState on the FSM Stack which is transformed into an GoapAction Queue in the current cycle. Calling the function again in the next one pushes a new IdleState on top of this generated action Queue, which renders the Queue obsolete and causes the Unit to not perform any action since the RunActionState is now beneath the newly pushed IdleState.

        Parameters:
        newGoapState - the new goal the unit tries to archive.
